  "title": "Setting Up Your Python Environment",
  "lessonText": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to prepare your Python environment for game development.",
  "data": {
    "content": "## Steps to Set Up Your Python Environment\n- **Install Python**: Download the latest version from the official website.\n- **Choose an IDE**: Select an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) like PyCharm or Visual Studio Code.\n- **Set Up Virtual Environment**: Use `venv` to create isolated environments for your projects.\n- **Install Pygame**: Run `pip install pygame` in your command line to add game development libraries.\n- **Verify Installation**: Check your setup by running a simple Python script."
  }
